BEFORE INSTALLING:

Necessary:
npm
node

Recommended:
nginx

INSTALLING:
cd to navapp directory
sudo npm install

KEY FILES:

./config/default-0.json:
Contains the configuration for the navapp server. 

./bin/install:
Runs immediately after "npm install".  Places configuration files from ./etc
to their appropriate places.  Installs pm2 globally using npm and attempts to
start pm2 and set up the system startup file.

./etc/autostart/autostart:
Script used by the Raspberry Pi on boot.
Turns off screensaver.  Starts browser in kiosk mode and starts X11VNC server.

./etc/nginx/navapp:
Server configuration file for the NGINX server that passes connections to the 
node server.



